          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LEAST",
                "INTAD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Cook least-square method for  (g,p)",
                " reaction  differential  cross section obtaining from",
                " (e,e'p) reaction cross sections measured  using  the",
                " direct   proton   detection   with   the   following",
                " integration over angles."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Root-mean-squared errors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Photoproton energy distributions have  been  measured",
                " for the  (e,e'p)  reaction at a number of bombarding",
                " energies. The results are  used  to  obtain  (e,e'p)",
                " cross sections and isochromats.  The  (e,e'p)  cross",
                " sections   are  analyzed  to  get  the  (g,p)  cross",
                " sections.  The results and (g,p) cross sections show",
                " a strong resonance around 25.0 MeV, whose energy and",
                " integrated cross section agree well with theory  for",
                " iar.  Proton  spectra  emitted  through  the IAR are",
                " extracted from the photoproton spectra and also from",
                " the  isochromats.  Strong proton groups are found at",
                " around 15.3 and 11 MeV corresponding  to  the  h11/2",
                " proton  hole  state  at  1.3  MeV  and  also neutron",
                " particle-hole states around 6 MeV  in  the  residual",
                " nucleus.  The  result  is  in  a good agreement with",
                " estimates obtained from proton scattering on  208Pb,",
                " showing the configuration of the iar states."
              ]
            }
          ],
